<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,1066,1301]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
As for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" box="[268,471,1066,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caurensis">
<emphasis box="[268,471,1066,1092]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Centris caurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the single male specimen used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[877,1075,1066,1092]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="167 - 221" refId="ref19848" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1919. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 3. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 55: 167 - 221. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.55 - 2264.167" type="journal article" year="1919">Cockerell (1919)</bibRefCitation>
to describe this species was also collected by Melbourne Carriker in the same locality. The 
<typeStatus box="[938,1041,1108,1134]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[1057,1143,1108,1134]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="24.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[189,1398,1470,1925]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Fig. 19. Centris fusciventris matoensis Cockerell, 1919, holotype, ♂ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534203). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3722986" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3722986/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) is housed at 
<collectionCode box="[1309,1399,1108,1134]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the following data label: Rio Mato Caura Dist Venez [printed] X.09 [handwritten]\ MACarriker collector [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ckll" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" box="[423,897,1191,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="fusciventris" variety="matoensis">
<emphasis box="[423,655,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Centris fusciventris</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[718,835,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">matoensis</emphasis>
Ckll
</taxonomicName>
Type [handwritten]\ [red label] Type No. [printed] 21654 [handwritten] 
<collectingCountry box="[561,611,1233,1259]" name="United States of America" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">U.S.</collectingCountry>
