<paragraph blockId="25.[189,1399,316,456]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation author="Cockerell" box="[189,390,316,342]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" pagination="167 - 221" refId="ref19848" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1919. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 3. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 55: 167 - 221. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.55 - 2264.167" type="journal article" year="1919">Cockerell (1919)</bibRefCitation>
cited a specimen also collected by M. Carriker at the 
<typeStatus box="[1038,1089,317,343]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fusciventris" subSpecies="caurensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. fusciventris caurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" box="[363,662,354,380]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="fusciventris" subSpecies="matoensis">
<emphasis box="[363,662,354,380]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. fusciventris matoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subvariety of the latter subspecies. The characters cited by him about the integument of the clypeus and the pubescence on the fourth tergum are within the variation range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1919" box="[405,557,430,456]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caurensis">
<emphasis box="[405,557,430,456]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">C. caurensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
